text: S/2006 S 3 is an unnamed moon of Saturn. Its discovery was announced by Scott S. Sheppard, David C. Jewitt, Jan Kleyna, and Brian G. Marsden on June 26, 2006, from observations taken between January and April 2006. S/2006 S 3 is about 6 kilometres in diameter, and orbits Saturn at an average distance of 21,076,300 km in 1142.366 days, at an inclination of 150.8° to the ecliptic (128.8° to Saturn's equator), with an eccentricity of 0.4710. == References == * Institute for Astronomy Saturn Satellite Data * IAUC 8727: Satellites of Saturn 2006 June 30 (discovery) * MPEC 2006-M45: Eight New Satellites of Saturn 2006 June 26 (discovery and ephemeris) Category:Saturn's moons
